# Sidebar Logo

The sidebar header logo switches based on sidebar mode:

- **Expanded (static):** `assets/opp/AppLogo/AppLogo-onDark_H.svg`
- **Compact:** `assets/opp/AppLogo/AppLogo-onDark_compact.svg`

Rules:

- Do NOT use `layout/images/logo-dark-horizontal.svg` or `layout/images/logo-light-horizontal.svg`.
- Do NOT switch logo based on light/dark theme — only based on sidebar mode.
- The `alt` text should remain `"UNOPS"`.
- `sidebarLogo` is a `computed()` signal — use `sidebarLogo()` in the template.

```html
<!-- ✅ Correct -->
<img class="logo-image" [src]="sidebarLogo()" alt="UNOPS" />

<!-- ❌ Wrong — switching based on theme -->
<img class="logo-image" [src]="isDarkTheme() ? '...' : '...'" alt="UNOPS" />
```
